Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getPinAssignMode(25.10)                                getPinAssignMode(25.10)

Name
       getPinAssignMode  -  Returns  information about the specified setPinAs-
       signMode parameter in the Innovus log file and the console

Syntax
       getPinAssignMode

       [-help]

       [-advance_node_rule_support]

       [-allow_unconnected_in_abutted_edge]

       [-allowNonNdrNetPinsOnNdrTracks]

       [-block_boundary_macro_distance]

       [-force_abutment_with_fixed]

       [-insidePinSearchDistance]

       [-max_distance_pairing]

       [-maxChannelWidthAsAbutted]

       [-maxLayer]

       [-minLayer]

       [-pinEditInBatch]

       [-pinOffStripe]

       [-pinToStripeDistance]

       [-pinToViaDistanceNonPrefDirection]

       [-pinToViaDistancePrefDirection]

       [-promotedMacroMaxLayer]

       [-promotedMacroMinLayer]

       [-restrict_boundary_macro_distance]

       [-strict_abutment]

       [-quiet]

       [-useCommonColorEngineForIO]

       Returns information about the specified setPinAssignMode  parameter  in
       the  Innovus log file and the console. The following information is re-
       turned:

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Whether the current value was set by user

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each getPinAssignMode parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command: man getPinAssignMode

       -parameter_names
              Displays information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify  one  or  more parameters. See setPinAssignMode for descrip-
              tions of the parameters you can specify.

       -quiet Displays the current settings for the  specified  parameters  in
              Tcl list format only.

Examples
              * The  following  command  returns  the current settings for the
                setPinAssignMode parameters:

                getPinAssignMode

                The software returns the following information:

                -advanced_node_rule_support true       # bool, default=true

                -allow_unconnected_in_abutted_edge   true      #   bool,   de-
                fault=true

                -allowNonNdrNetPinsOnNdrTracks true    # bool, default=true

                -block_boundary_macro_distance  3        #  float,  default=3,
                min=0, max=100

                -force_abutment_with_fixed true        # bool, default=true

                -insidePinSearchDistance  10             #  int,   default=10,
                min=1, max=100

                -max_distance_pairing  50                #  float, default=50,
                min=0, max=10000

                -maxChannelWidthAsAbutted  3             #  float,  default=3,
                min=0, max=400

                -pinEditInBatch false                  # bool, default=false

                -pinOffStripe   none                      #  enums={below  all
                none}, default=none

                -pinToStripeDistance {}                # string, default=""

                -pinToViaDistanceNonPrefDirection {}   # string, default=""

                -pinToViaDistancePrefDirection {}      # string, default=""

                -promotedMacroMaxLayer 31              # string, default=31

                -promotedMacroMinLayer 31              # string, default=31

                -restrict_boundary_macro_distance 30    #  float,  default=30,
                min=0, max=100

                -strict_abutment true                  # bool, default=true

                -useCommonColorEngineForIO false       # bool, default=false

                {advanced_node_rule_support         true}        {allow_uncon-
                nected_in_abutted_edge  true}   {allowNonNdrNetPinsOnNdrTracks
                true}     {block_boundary_macro_distance    3}    {force_abut-
                ment_with_fixed true} {insidePinSearchDistance  10}  {max_dis-
                tance_pairing 50} {maxChannelWidthAsAbutted 3} {pinEditInBatch
                false}  {pinOffStripe  none}  {pinToStripeDistance  {}}  {pin-
                ToViaDistanceNonPrefDirection {}}  {pinToViaDistancePrefDirec-
                tion {}} {promotedMacroMaxLayer 31} {promotedMacroMinLayer 31}
                {restrict_boundary_macro_distance  30}  {strict_abutment true}
                {useCommonColorEngineForIO false}

